The paper discusses a modular model for data publication with a focus on provenance, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category as the paper deals with data publication and integrity checking. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely categories as the paper discusses the Semantic Web and query answering. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is another possible category as the paper deals with data publication and aggregation. Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design patterns used in the ovopub model.
